==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|weke-dai}}, {{m|enm|wikdai}}, {{m|enm|wokdai}}, {{m|enm|wokedai}}, {{m|enm|wockedai}}, {{m|enm|woukedai}}, {{m|enm|wukedaȝȝ}}, equivalent to {{compound|en|week|day}}. Compare {{cog|fy|wikedei||weekday}}, {{cog|nl|weekdag||weekday}}, {{cog|de|Wochentag||weekday}}, {{cog|da|ugedag||weekday}}, {{cog|sv|veckodag||weekday}}, {{cog|no|ukedag||weekday}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-weekday.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A day of the week except those which form the [[weekend]]; that is:
## Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday or Friday, but not Saturday or Sunday.
## Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, or Saturday, but not Sunday. {{rfex|lang=en}}
## {{lb|en|Judaism}} Sunday, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday or Friday, but not Saturday.

